Halve and peel the @onion{1}. Finely chop half and cut the other half into thin slices.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @lemon{1}.

Quarter the @mushrooms{150%g}, halving any larger quarters.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Drain the @grilling cheese{200%g} then cut it into 1cm cubes. Place cubes in a #bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Place a #pot{} with a tight-fitting lid over medium-high heat with @butter{1/2%tbsp}.

When hot, fry the finely chopped onion for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @rice{150%g}, @vegetable stock{1%sachet} and @water{300%ml}(cold, salted).

Bring to the boil then lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid.

Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for ~{10%minutes} more (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Spiced Vegetables ==

Meanwhile, place a pan over medium-high heat with @butter{1/2%tbsp}.

Once hot, fry the garlic and sliced onion for ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @Middle Eastern Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @pepper{to taste} and mushrooms and fry on high heat for ~{6-8%minutes}.

Add @lemon juice{2%tsp} and season to taste with @salt{to taste} and pepper.

Transfer from the pan and cover to keep warm.

== Golden Fried Cheese ==

Remove the cheese from the water, pop onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and pat dry.

Wipe the pan and return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the grilling cheese until golden, shifting frequently, ~{4-5%minutes}.

== Yoghurt Sauce ==

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @coriander{10%g}(stalks and all).

In a bowl, mix half the coriander with the @yoghurt{75%g}, @dried chilli flakes{1%sachet}, @lemon juice{2%tsp} and @oil{1/2%tbsp}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> Use less chilli flakes if you don't like spice.

== To Serve ==

Divide the rice between bowls and spoon over the spiced veg.

Arrange cubes of golden grilling cheese on top.

Garnish with the yoghurt sauce and remaining coriander.